ng the next three years, Sears will look more like a mass merchant, with mo=
re self-serve areas and centralized checkouts.=20
As part of its financial realignment, Sears will cut 4,900 jobs in the next=
 18 months.=20
The company's challenge, analysts say, is to offer something unique within =
its niche of serving middle-income consumers--an ever difficult proposition=
 against innovative rivals such as Kohl's and Target.=20
